# ALL PROGRAMS ARE WRITTEN FOR REVERSE OF A NUMBER
# ALL PROGRAMS ARE WRITTEN ON THE DIFFICULTY LEVELS TO REVERSE THE SERIES
# ALL PROGRAMS ARE WRITTEN IN THE USER INPUT FORMAT 



# Program 1: Using loop
n = int(input("Enter a number to reverse: "))
rev = 0
while n > 0:
    rev = rev*10 + n%10
    n //= 10
print("Reversed number =", rev)

# output:
# Enter a number to reverse: 3746
# Reversed number = 6473






# Program 2: Using string slicing
n = input("Enter a number to reverse: ")
print("Reversed number =", n[::-1])

# OUTPUT:
# Enter a number to reverse: 7383
# Reversed number = 3837





# Program 3: Reverse list of numbers
numbers = list(map(int, input("Enter numbers separated by space: ").split()))
rev_list = [int(str(x)[::-1]) for x in numbers]
print("Reversed list =", rev_list)

# OUTPUT:
# Enter numbers separated by space: 65
# Reversed list = [56]